Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 59, 11? Name Philainios. From same die as Pergamon AS63?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0856)
